    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "header"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Gemini Data Analytics: A2A SDK API Sample\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook demonstrates how to interact with the **DataA2AService** using gRPC. Since a high-level SDK is being finalized, we will generate the client code directly from the A2A protocol buffers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "background-and-overview"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Background and Overview\n",
        "The **Conversational Analytics API** (also known as Gemini Data Analytics) lets you chat with your BigQuery or Looker data anywhere. This notebook demonstrates how to use the **A2A (Agent-to-Agent)** interface via gRPC and generated client code. Since a high-level SDK is being finalized, we will generate the client code directly from the A2A protocol buffers.\n",
        "\n",
        "This is a **Pre-GA** product. See [documentation](https://cloud.google.com/gemini/docs/conversational-analytics-api/overview) for more details.\n",
        "\n",
        "Please provide feedback to conversational-analytics-api-feedback@google.com\n",
        "<br>\n",
        "### This notebook will help you\n",
        "1. Authenticate to Google Cloud and Setup Environment\n",
        "2. Download and Compile A2A Protos\n",
        "3. Implement a gRPC Client for DataA2AService\n",
        "4. Receive real-time streaming updates (Messages, Artifacts)\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "setup"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# @title 1. Environment Setup\n",
        "# Install gRPC dependencies\n",
        "%pip install grpcio grpcio-tools google-auth requests\n",
        "\n",
        "import os\n",
        "import time\n",
        "import uuid\n",
        from google.auth import default\n",
        "from google.auth.transport.requests import Request\n",
        "from google.colab import auth\n",
        "import grpc\n",
        "\n",
        "# Authenticate the user\n",
        "auth.authenticate_user()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get credentials and project ID\n",
        "creds, project_id = default()\n",
        "creds.refresh(Request())\n",
        "access_token = creds.token\n",
        "\n",
        "ENDPOINT = \"geminidataanalytics.googleapis.com:443\"\n",
        "LOCATION = \"global\"  # @param {type:\"string\"}\n",
        "AGENT_ID = \"bigquery-ca\"  # @param {type:\"string\"}\n",
        "TENANT = f\"projects/{project_id}/locations/{LOCATION}/dataAgents/{AGENT_ID}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Target Tenant: {TENANT}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "proto-gen-header"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 2. Proto Generation\n",
        "\n",
        "We fetch the A2A specification from the official repository and generate the Python client code."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "proto-gen-code"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# @title Download and Compile Protos\n",
        "import os\n",
        "import subprocess\n",
        "import grpc_tools.protoc\n",
        "\n",
        "PROTO_URL = \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/a2aproject/a2a/main/specification/grpc/a2a.proto\"\n",
        "PROTO_FILE = \"a2a.proto\"\n",
        "OUT_DIR = os.getcwd()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Download specification\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(PROTO_FILE):\n",
        "  subprocess.run([\"wget\", \"-q\", PROTO_URL], check=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "if not os.path.exists(PROTO_FILE):\n",
        "  raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Failed to download {PROTO_FILE}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Compile using absolute paths for output\n",
        "ret = grpc_tools.protoc.main([\n",
        "    \"grpc_tools.protoc\",\n",
        "    f\"-I{OUT_DIR}\",\n",
        "    f\"--python_out={OUT_DIR}\",\n",
        "    f\"--grpc_python_out={OUT_DIR}\",\n",
        "    os.path.join(OUT_DIR, PROTO_FILE),\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "if ret != 0:\n",
        "  raise RuntimeError(f\"protoc failed with exit code {ret}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "import a2a_pb2\n",
        "import a2a_pb2_grpc\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"A2A Protos compiled and imported successfully.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "grpc-client-header"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 3. Implementation: A2A gRPC Client\n",
        "\n",
        "Here we implement a wrapper for the `DataA2AService` to handle authentication and response parsing."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "grpc-client-code"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "class DataA2AClient:\n",
        "\n",
        "  def __init__(self, endpoint, token):\n",
        "    # Create secure channel with OAuth2 token\n",
        "    call_creds = grpc.access_token_call_credentials(token)\n",
        "    channel_creds = grpc.composite_channel_credentials(\n",
        "        grpc.ssl_channel_credentials(), call_creds\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    self.channel = grpc.secure_channel(endpoint, channel_creds)\n",
        "    # Note: The service is aliased as DataA2AService on the endpoint\n",
        "    self.stub = a2a_pb2_grpc.A2AServiceStub(self.channel)\n",
        "\n",
        "  def get_agent_card(self, tenant):\n",
        "    request = a2a_pb2.GetAgentCardRequest(tenant=tenant)\n",
        "    return self.stub.GetAgentCard(request)\n",
        "\n",
        "  def send_message(self, tenant, text, blocking=True):\n",
        "    request = a2a_pb2.SendMessageRequest(\n",
        "        tenant=tenant,\n",
        "        request=a2a_pb2.Message(\n",
        "            message_id=f\"msg-{uuid.uuid4()}\",\n",
        "            role=a2a_pb2.ROLE_USER, content=[a2a_pb2.Part(text=text)]\n",
        "        ),\n",
        "        configuration=a2a_pb2.SendMessageConfiguration(blocking=blocking),\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    return self.stub.SendMessage(request)\n",
        "\n",
        "  def send_streaming_message(self, tenant, text):\n",
        "    request = a2a_pb2.SendMessageRequest(\n",
        "        tenant=tenant,\n",
        "        request=a2a_pb2.Message(\n",
        "            message_id=f\"msg-{uuid.uuid4()}\",\n",
        "            role=a2a_pb2.ROLE_USER, content=[a2a_pb2.Part(text=text)]\n",
        "        ),\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    return self.stub.SendStreamingMessage(request)\n",
        "\n",
        "  def subscribe_to_task(self, task_id):\n",
        "    request = a2a_pb2.TaskSubscriptionRequest(name=f\"tasks/{task_id}\")\n",
        "    return self.stub.TaskSubscription(request)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "client = DataA2AClient(ENDPOINT, access_token)\n",
        "print(\"Client initialized.\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "streaming-demo-header"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 4. Example: Real-time Streaming\n",
        "\n",
        "We can now receive updates (Task status, Messages, and Artifacts) in real-time."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "streaming-demo-code"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "query = \"Show me sales trends for 2025\"\n",
        "print(f\"Sending streaming request: {query}\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "try:\n",
        "  for response in client.send_streaming_message(TENANT, query):\n",
        "    if response.HasField(\"status_update\"):\n",
        "      print(f\"[Status] {response.status_update.status.state}\")\n",
        "    elif response.HasField(\"artifact_update\"):\n",
        "      art = response.artifact_update.artifact\n",
        "      print(f\"[Artifact] {art.name}: {art.description}\")\n",
        "    elif response.HasField(\"msg\"):\n",
        "      print(f\"[Message] {response.msg.content[0].text}\")\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "  print(f\"Error: {e}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cleanup-header"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 5. Cleanup\n",
        "\n",
